<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="656" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.00/93</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chilton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Manchester, Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-20"><hi rend="italic">July
                                        20, 1925.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 21.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 703</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to refer to my
                            immediately preceding notes regarding the reply to be returned by the
                            Diplomatic Body at Peking to the representations addressed to them by
                            the Chinese Government on June 24th last.</p>
                        <p>His Majesty’s Government now inform me that the Italian proposal, to
                            which reference was made in paragraph two of my note No. 701, is that
                            the identic reply by the Powers to the above-mentioned Chinese
                            representations should embody and itself constitute the public
                            declaration previously suggested by His Majesty’s Government.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>(For His Majesty’s Minister)<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John
                                    Balfour</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>